This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the task of recommendation, which is a common application of IR. The paper also proposes a neural network architecture to address the challenges of shared-account and cross-domain sequential recommendation, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques to process user behavior data, which is relevant to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also deals with the problem of discriminating behaviors from one domain that might be helpful to improve recommendations in the other domains, which falls under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of parallel computing techniques to improve the efficiency of the proposed model, which is relevant to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
